      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 2024: loadMissingBodyOverwrites() only writes back non-empty plugin results and leaves messages with no overwrite unmarked. Because the selection criterion is `!msg-\u003epluginData.contains(\"bodyOverwrite\")`, plugins that legitimately return no overwrite will be called again on every load/reload path for the same messages, causing repeated unnecessary transforms and signals for large histories. Store a sentinel/empty entry or track that the message has already been processed separately from the overwrite value.\n\n```suggestion\nsignalMsg \u003d injectEditionOverwrites(transformed.id,\n    boIt !\u003d transformed.pluginData.end() ? boIt-\u003esecond : std::string_view {});\n```\nIf empty values mean \"processed but no overwrite\", update injectEditionOverwrites() or the selection predicate to distinguish that state from missing data.",
      "revId": "bab93ce252d97db9d447f464eaf48b50ac6aca00",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
